"The user starts with View 1 at the [Overview] level to explore aggregated metrics grouped by customer status in the database. Next, the user selects specific customer statuses of interest in View 1, impacting other views. View 2 [Exploration] displays demographic distributions for selected groups, while View 3 allows exploration of correlations between satisfaction, churn scores, and CLTV via scatter plots. Interactions in View 3 further lead to detailed drill-down analysis of outliers in satisfaction and churn scores within View 5. The user studies geographic clusters within View 4 [Detail] for location-based patterns, and finally generates summarized insights on anomalies in View 6."